                            <comment id="16371120" author="apachespark" created="Wed, 21 Feb 2018 09:11:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;viirya&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/20648&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/20648&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16375386" author="apachespark" created="Sat, 24 Feb 2018 07:41:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;viirya&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/20666&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/20666&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16375439" author="viirya" created="Sat, 24 Feb 2018 09:18:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In fact this is exactly the JSON parser&apos;s behavior, not a bug. We don&apos;t allow partial result for corrupted records. Except for the field configured by &lt;tt&gt;columnNameOfCorruptRecord&lt;/tt&gt;, all fields will be set to &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
